  "Partial EUC-JP (JIS X 0212 supplementary) → Unicode mapping table.

JIS X 0212 = not encodable in Shift-JIS; EUC-JP only (CS3
codeset, 3-byte sequence: 0x8F + lead + trail).

Entry count = 64 (MVP subset). Full ~6000 entries are deferred
to the Phase 7.5 generator.

Schema = alist of (EUC-INT . CODEPOINT) cons cells, where
EUC-INT = (lead << 8) | trail (= the 0x8F prefix is implicit
and added by the codec at encode time).

Provenance: docs/coding-table-provenance.org §3 JIS X 0212.")

(defconst nelisp-coding-jis-tables-sha256
  "eb0e024fd054b293edc263868d3f0d3358af2892fdd6a84f882104f435b590cc"
  "Golden SHA-256 hash of the four JIS partial tables, concatenated and
prin1-formatted in declaration order:

  1. `nelisp-coding-shift-jis-x0208-decode-table'
  2. `nelisp-coding-cp932-extension-decode-table'
  3. `nelisp-coding-euc-jp-x0208-decode-table'
  4. `nelisp-coding-euc-jp-x0212-decode-table'

CI で改竄検出 (Doc 31 v2 §6.10 + §7.2).
Phase 7.5 で tools/coding-table-gen.el が real 14000 entry table
を生成した時点で本値は再計算されて update される.

Compute / verify with `nelisp-coding-jis-tables-verify-hash'.")

(defun nelisp-coding-jis-tables--canonical-bytes ()
  "Return the canonical byte sequence used to compute the golden hash.
This is the prin1-formatted concatenation of the four partial tables
in declaration order. Encapsulated as a function so the same canonical
serialization is used at table-write time (in `tools/coding-table-gen.el')
and at runtime verification."
  (concat
   (prin1-to-string nelisp-coding-shift-jis-x0208-decode-table)
   (prin1-to-string nelisp-coding-cp932-extension-decode-table)
   (prin1-to-string nelisp-coding-euc-jp-x0208-decode-table)
   (prin1-to-string nelisp-coding-euc-jp-x0212-decode-table)))

(defun nelisp-coding-jis-tables-verify-hash ()
  "Compute current table content SHA-256 and compare with the golden hash.

Returns t on match. On mismatch, signals `nelisp-coding-table-corruption'
with data plist `(:expected GOLDEN :actual COMPUTED)'.

The check guards against accidental table mutation (= a rebase / merge
that silently rewrites entries)。Per Doc 31 v2 §6.10 + §7.2, this hash is
treated as part of the file contract and must be re-computed whenever the
table content changes (typically by re-running `tools/coding-table-gen.el')."
  (let ((computed (secure-hash 'sha256
                               (nelisp-coding-jis-tables--canonical-bytes))))
    (if (equal computed nelisp-coding-jis-tables-sha256)
        t
      (signal 'nelisp-coding-table-corruption
              (list :expected nelisp-coding-jis-tables-sha256
                    :actual computed)))))

